  "bio_raw": "Currently, Mr. N M Baki Billah is working as a Senior Lecturer & E/MBA Program Coordinator at ULAB School of Business. Before joining ULAB, he had served as Assistant Dean & Lecturer at BRAC Business School, BRAC University. In addition to his other substantial administrative responsibilities at BRAC University, he taught more than four years at the undergraduate level. Before becoming a full-time faculty member, he also took courses at BRAC University & Presidency University as an adjunct faculty member. Prior to being in academics, he worked as an Associate Consultant & Research Analyst in Institute for Customer Relationship Management (iCRM), Malaysia; which was a MSC status premier knowledge company in Malaysia. In that role his primary areas of responsibility covered: Consumer Analytics, Big Data Visualization, Market Segmentation Research.\nHe teaches Finance subjects such as Financial Management, Security Analysis & Portfolio Management, Corporate Finance at both undergraduate and postgraduate levels. His research interests are in the areas of Corporate Finance, Financial Statement Analysis for Decision Making, Security Analysis, Portfolio Management, Analysis of financial institutions.",
  "stated_interests": [
    "Corporate Finance, Financial Statement Analysis for Decision Making, Security Analysis, Portfolio Management, Analysis of financial institutions."
  ],
  "education": [
    {
      "raw": "Education\nM\naster of Business Administration, 2014, “\nBest Masters Student of the Year”\nGraduate School of Business\nNational University of Malaysia (UKM-GSB)\nAccredited by AACSB & ABEST21, Member (AAPBS, EFMD).\nBachelor of Business Administration, 2012, “\nSumma Cum laude”\nDepartment of Business Administration\nEast West University, Dhaka, Bangladesh.\nSpecialization\nFinance"
    }
  ],
  "publications_raw": [
    "Journal Articles\nMcGowan, Carl B., Billah, N. M. Baki, Yakob, Noor Azuddin. (2015). ‘Liquidity Analysis of Selected Public-Listed Companies in Malaysia’. International Economics and Business-Macrothink Institute, USA. Vol. 1, No. 1, DOI: http://dx.doi.org/10.5296/ieb.v1i1.7508",
    "Conference Proceedings\nBillah, N. M. Baki, Tanvir K. M. N. I.  (2017, September). Performance Appraisal using CAMEL Approach: A Comparative Study of Publicly Traded Banks in Bangladesh. Paper presented at the International Conference on Business and Management 2017, Dhaka, Bangladesh.\nhttp://icbm.bracu.ac.bd/icbm-2017/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/ICBM-2017-Conference-Proceedings-ISBN-978-984-34-2360-3-Online-Version.pdf\nHasan, R., Rahman, K., Sakina, K. Billah, N.M. Baki (2019).  Country risk and its significance in context of Bangladesh. Paper presented at the International Conference on Business and Management 2019, Dhaka, Bangladesh. http://icbm.bracu.ac.bd/conference-proceedings",
    "Works\nSenior Lecturer (October 2019 – Present), School of Business, University of Liberal Arts Bangladesh (ULAB), Dhaka, Bangladesh\nPreparing course outlines, course calendars and lesson plans; conducting theoretical and tutorial classes for undergraduate students.\nProviding proper academic and professional advising or counseling to designated advisees and to students in any of his courses.\nPreparing and marking student assignments, essays, exams and encouraging students to use one-on-one feedback to gain conceptual understanding.\nPlanning and executing classroom-based experiential learning exercises, including but not limited to: role-playing, games, case studies, presentations and various types of group work.\nConducting research, not only for pure academic purposes but also for developing ingenious teaching approaches and teaching materials to enthuse students.\nAssistant Dean & Lecturer (August 2016 – September 2019), BRAC Business School, BRAC University, 66 Mohakhali, Dhaka 1212, Bangladesh\nUndertaking Finance courses at undergraduate level. Providing thorough advice to students regarding academic aspects and professional development. Supervising students’ research activities. Carrying out administrative tasks related to department, such as annual report compilation, undergraduate admission, internship coordination.\nAdjunct Faculty (January 2016 – July 2016), BRAC Business School, BRAC University, 66 Mohakhali, Dhaka 1212, Bangladesh\nUndertaking Finance courses at undergraduate level. Providing thorough advice to students regarding academic aspects and professional development.\nAdjunct Faculty (May 2016 – July 2016), Department of Civil Engineering (CE), Presidency University, Gulshan-2, Dhaka 1212\nDelivering lectures and designing course materials at undergraduate level for civil engineering students. Encouraging students to develop operational research and statistical skills for real projects via tutorial work.\nDate: 08/01/2019"
  ],
